{"componentChunkName":"component---src-components-day-template-js","path":"/day-3","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Simple Login with useContext hooks","day":"3","publishDate":"2020-08-11","shareText":"Learning about useContext hooks. ðŸ˜Š","hashtags":["100DaysOfCode","Context","React","Hooks","useContext","useHistory","Reac_Router_Dom","useState"],"thumbnailImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.3157894736842106,"src":"/static/c91df8813863181a5fa0ff974e4434af/3891b/day-3.png","srcSet":"/static/c91df8813863181a5fa0ff974e4434af/3ba9f/day-3.png 100w,\n/static/c91df8813863181a5fa0ff974e4434af/8ac63/day-3.png 200w,\n/static/c91df8813863181a5fa0ff974e4434af/3891b/day-3.png 400w,\n/static/c91df8813863181a5fa0ff974e4434af/8c332/day-3.png 600w,\n/static/c91df8813863181a5fa0ff974e4434af/fb5f3/day-3.png 602w","sizes":"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"}}}},"html":"<h2>Notes:</h2>\n<hr>\n<ul>\n<li>Global data in React JS.</li>\n<li>Exchange data between components without props method.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>React useContext hooks:</h2>\n<hr>\n<h3>The login problem:</h3>\n<h4>Description:</h4>\n<p>This problem is about exchanged user data between brothers component into a simple app. The objective is only to use the concept about context in react using hooks.</p>\n<h4>Step 1.</h4>\n<p>The first thing to do is create a context that you want to share between all yours components. Create    <code>UserContext.js</code> file.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code>const UserContext = React.createContext(initialValue);</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code>export default UserContext;</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<h4>Step 2.</h4>\n<p>Later you need to wrap the father of all componentes between <code>UserContext.Provider</code> High Order Component (HOC). You can do this in <code>Main.js</code> .</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Create <code>useState</code> hook:<br>\n<code>const [user, setUser] = useState({});</code></li>\n<li>Create <code>userInfo</code> objet:<br>\n<code>const userInfo = { user, setUser };</code></li>\n<li>Use the <code>userInfo</code> object in the <code>value</code> props:  </li>\n</ul>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code>&#x3C;UserContext.Provider value= { userInfo }></code>  </p>\n</blockquote>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code>&#x3C;ChildrensComponents /></code>   </p>\n</blockquote>\n</blockquote>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code>&#x3C;/UserContext.Provider></code></p>\n</blockquote>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<h4>Note:</h4>\n<p>The userInfo is object and you can save functions and others js stuffs that you need more forward.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h4>Step 3.</h4>\n<p> Finally you can import <code>UserContext</code> in all you components, here into in action the useContext hooks. This hooks need the <code>UserContext</code> like initial props.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code>const {user, setUser} = useContext(UserContext);</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>You can check out <a href='https://github.com/difo23/hooks-app' target=\"_blank\"> Github page </a> code <a href= 'https://github.com/difo23/hooks-app'> by @difo23 </a> </p>"},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Lizandro's 100 Days of Code"}}},"pageContext":{"day":"3","title":"Simple Login with useContext hooks"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1497828201","63159454"]}